-- Slovak Republic Said to Hire Banks for Future Euro Bond Sale
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-01-11T09:46:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/slovak-republic-said-to-hire-banks-for-future-euro-bond-sale.html
The Slovak Republic hired  HSBC
Holdings Plc. (HSBA) , Societe Generale SA,  Tatra Banka AS (TAT)  and  UniCredit
SpA (UCG)  to manage a benchmark bond issue in euros, which will take
place when market conditions allow, according to a banker
involved in the transaction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
